    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="400"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Francis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1901</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 14.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that I was accorded a
                    special audience to-day by King Alexander, upon which occasion His Majesty
                    presented me to Her Majesty, Queen Draga. They both declared in strongest terms
                    their horror at the murder of President McKinley and their sympathy for the
                    American people in the great loss they have sustained by the death of a chief so
                    wise and so good. Their majesties inquired particularly about Mrs. McKinley, and
                    expressed for her the tenderest solicitude. King Alexander was evidently much
                    gratified when I informed him that I had been requested by my Government in a
                    cable dispatch received last evening to convey to His Majesty Mrs. McKinley’s
                    sincerest appreciation of his message of condolence.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles S. Francis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
